The paper deals with the task of gaze estimation from single eye input using a deep neural network architecture. This task involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as image processing and feature extraction, which are commonly used in the cs.CV sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach using an intermediate pictorial representation, which involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as deep neural networks, making it likely to belong to the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The task of gaze estimation also has applications in human-computer interaction (HCI), making it relevant to the cs.HC sub-category. Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on real-world images, which involves multimedia (MM) techniques such as image and video processing, making it relevant to the cs.MM sub-category.
